# wikisnap cron examples
# -----------------------
# This file shows how to schedule automatic Wikipedia snapshots
# and periodic change detection using cron.
#
# Before using:
# 1. Update the paths below to match your system.
# 2. Run: crontab -e
# 3. Paste the desired job into your crontab.
#
# Make sure your virtual environment exists and dependencies are installed:
#   python3 -m venv ~/wikisnap/.venv
#   source ~/wikisnap/.venv/bin/activate
#   pip install -r ~/wikisnap/requirements.txt


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Example 1: Run wikisnap daily at 02:00 AM
# ------------------------------------------------------------
0 2 * * * /home/USER/wikisnap/.venv/bin/python \
/home/USER/wikisnap/bin/wikisnap \
-i /home/USER/wikisnap/example/urls.csv \
-o /home/USER/wikisnap/snapshots >> /home/USER/wikisnap/cron.log 2>&1


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Example 2: Run diffcheck daily at 02:30 AM (compare with 1 day ago)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
30 2 * * * /home/USER/wikisnap/.venv/bin/python \
/home/USER/wikisnap/bin/diffcheck \
-o /home/USER/wikisnap/snapshots \
-n 1 >> /home/USER/wikisnap/cron.log 2>&1


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Example 3: Weekly snapshot (Sunday at 03:00 AM)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
0 3 * * 0 /home/USER/wikisnap/.venv/bin/python \
/home/USER/wikisnap/bin/wikisnap \
-i /home/USER/wikisnap/example/urls.csv \
-o /home/USER/wikisnap/snapshots >> /home/USER/wikisnap/cron.log 2>&1


# Notes:
# - Replace USER with your actual username.
# - Use full absolute paths (cron does NOT load your shell profile).
# - Output is appended to cron.log for debugging.
# - Test manually before enabling in cron.
